# Vantage Transformation Schema (v0.1)

This schema defines how concepts from Vantage A are mapped into Vantage B. 
Used for programmatic conflict detection across ADRs.

```json
{
  "version": "0.1",
  "transformations": [
    {
      "source_vantage": "Physicist",
      "target_vantage": "Economist",
      "rule": "equilibrium_adjust -> price_signal",
      "justification": "Invariance of state stability; Physicist observes flux, Economist observes signal.",
      "provenance": "[TRAINED]"
    },
    {
      "source_vantage": "Economist",
      "target_vantage": "Security",
      "rule": "incentive_alignment -> trust_anchor",
      "justification": "Invariance of system integrity; Economist models actors, Security models anchors.",
      "provenance": "[UNTRAINED]"
    },
    {
      "source_vantage": "Security",
      "target_vantage": "Physicist",
      "rule": "trust_anchor_hijack -> entropy_increase",
      "justification": "Invariance of information flow; Security observes integrity breach, Physicist observes disorder/entropy.",
      "provenance": "[UNTRAINED]"
    }
  ]
}
```
